A 16-year-old high school student in the Northern Cape has come up with a fresh way of collecting crime-scene forensic data. Currently, forensic investigators use a solution called Luminol to detect bloodstains at crime scenes. But this can give false reactions – potentially hampering crime investigations. Hoërskool Douglas learner Miné Steenkamp’s solution combines Luminol with Malaria fighting medication. Watch video below for more: 